					<div class="post-thumbnail-caption hero-video-caption">Harvesting <em>Artemia franciscana</em>, aka sea monkeys, from Utah’s Great Salt Lake for fish food was a key transformation in fish aquaculture. Video by antpke/Pond5</div>

					
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">Saving a Sea Monkey Sanctuary</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">As the Great Salt Lake in Utah shrinks, locals are working to preserve its critical brine shrimp fishery—along with the other entities that flourish in the lake’s strange, saline beauty.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/paul-greenberg/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Paul Greenberg</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
