							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/paul-greenberg/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Paul Greenberg is the author of the James Beard Award–winning, <em>New York Times</em> bestseller <em>Four Fish</em> and <em>American Catch</em>. He is also a regular contributor to the<em> New York Times</em> and has written for <em>National Geographic</em>, <em>GQ</em>, <em>The Times</em> (of London), and <em>Vogue</em>. He lectures on seafood and the environment around the world. Greenberg is currently a fellow with the Safina Center and a Pew Fellow in marine conservation.</p></div>
